<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="149" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,762,2011]" box="[199,758,906,931]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,906,931]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">Description.</emphasis>
BL: 
<quantity box="[401,537,907,931]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.55" metricValueMax="2.8" metricValueMin="2.3" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" unit="mm" value="2.55" valueMax="2.8" valueMin="2.3">2.3–2.8 mm</quantity>
BW: 
<quantity box="[602,754,906,931]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.4" metricValueMax="5.8" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" unit="mm" value="0.54" valueMax="0.58" valueMin="0.5">0.5–0.58 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,762,2011]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">Male. Body dark brown to black, with the apex of antennae, maxillary and labial palps, and legs light brown. Elytra entirely brown to black. Body subcylindrical and covered with fine microsetae. Dorsum of head, pronotum and elytra with sculpturing.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,762,2011]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">
Antennae with antennomeres 
<number box="[538,580,1050,1075]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" value="4.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="3.0">3–6</number>
with the same width and 
<number box="[878,933,1051,1075]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" value="9.0" valueMax="11.0" valueMin="7.0">7–11</number>
slightly increasing in width, antennomere 
<number box="[1422,1436,1050,1075]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" value="6.0">6</number>
the shortest. Clypeus with anterior margin slightly sinuate. Epistomal suture arcuate. Labrum transverse, anterior margin slightly sinuate. Cuticular process of internal fringe of epipharyngeal lobes with apex not serrated. Mandibles tridentate. Mentum subquadrate. Submentum extending onto venter of head, posterior margin strongly V-shaped. Gular sutures fused posteriorly. Pronotum convex, wider than long (PW/PL: 
<number box="[1169,1221,1195,1219]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" value="1.72">1.72</number>
), anterior pronotal angles produced, posterior margin curved. Prototergosternal suture present, procoxal fissure open, protrochantin exposed. Elytra as long as wide (EL/BW: 
<number box="[654,667,1267,1291]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" value="1.0">1</number>
), elytral epipleural ridge present and complete. Sternite VII with median lobe on posterior margin. Tergite VIII with a broad emargination on both sides near the anterior angle and posterior margin truncate. Posterior margin of sternite VIII slightly emarginated. Tergite IX with ventral struts. Tergite X with a dorsal depression on its posterior three-fourths (
<figureCitation box="[883,965,1374,1399]" captionStart="FIGURES 12 – 15" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1190,1213]" captionTargetBox="[153,1426,194,1168]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,193,1169]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 12 – 15. Bledius depressus, sp. nov.. 12, tergite X (detail of dorsal depression); 13, tergite X magnified (detail of the long membranous projection); 14, aedeagus, lateral view (detail of pair of sclerites); 15, spermatheca. Scale = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/256528/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">
Fig. 
<number box="[935,965,1375,1399]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" value="12.0">12</number>
</figureCitation>
, arrow), and posterior margin with a long membranous projection (
<figureCitation box="[437,522,1410,1435]" captionStart="FIGURES 12 – 15" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1190,1213]" captionTargetBox="[153,1426,194,1168]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,193,1169]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 12 – 15. Bledius depressus, sp. nov.. 12, tergite X (detail of dorsal depression); 13, tergite X magnified (detail of the long membranous projection); 14, aedeagus, lateral view (detail of pair of sclerites); 15, spermatheca. Scale = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/256528/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">
Fig. 
<number box="[492,522,1411,1435]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" value="13.0">13</number>
</figureCitation>
, arrow). Aedeagus with apex of the median lobe curved in lateral view and an evident pair of sclerites on the bulb base (
<figureCitation box="[618,700,1446,1471]" captionStart="FIGURES 12 – 15" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1190,1213]" captionTargetBox="[153,1426,194,1168]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,193,1169]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 12 – 15. Bledius depressus, sp. nov.. 12, tergite X (detail of dorsal depression); 13, tergite X magnified (detail of the long membranous projection); 14, aedeagus, lateral view (detail of pair of sclerites); 15, spermatheca. Scale = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/256528/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">
Fig. 
<number box="[670,700,1447,1471]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" value="14.0">14</number>
</figureCitation>
, arrow).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,762,2011]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">
Female. Similar to male except posterior margin of sternite VII truncate, without median lobe. Spermatheca with annelidoid form and the base bulbous and it is 
<number box="[731,816,1518,1543]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" value="2.75" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.5">2.5 to 3</number>
times longer than wider (
<figureCitation box="[1103,1187,1518,1543]" captionStart="FIGURES 12 – 15" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1190,1213]" captionTargetBox="[153,1426,194,1168]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,193,1169]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 12 – 15. Bledius depressus, sp. nov.. 12, tergite X (detail of dorsal depression); 13, tergite X magnified (detail of the long membranous projection); 14, aedeagus, lateral view (detail of pair of sclerites); 15, spermatheca. Scale = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/256528/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">
Fig. 
<number box="[1156,1187,1518,1543]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" value="15.0">15</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
