<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="149" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,762,2011]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1626,1651]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name is a Latin adjective that refers to the dorsal longitudinal depression on the posterior three-fourths of tergite X.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="150" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,762,2011]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1698,1723]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">Remarks.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[324,533,1699,1723]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">
<taxonomicName box="[324,528,1699,1723]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Bledius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="depressus" status="sp. nov.">Bledius depressus</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[542,633,1698,1723]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[542,633,1698,1723]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
was previously identified as 
<taxonomicName box="[970,1142,1699,1723]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Bledius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caribbeanus">
<emphasis box="[970,1142,1699,1723]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">B. caribbeanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Rosa" box="[1158,1351,1699,1723]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" refString="Rosa, L. C., Caron, E. &amp; Sousa-Souto, L. (2013) First record of Bledius caribbeanus Blackwelder, 1943 (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Oxytelinae) from Brazil and distributional extension of B. hermani Caron and Ribeiro-Costa, 2007. Checklist, 8 (6), 1321 - 1322. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.15560 / 9.2.450" type="journal article" year="2013">
Rosa 
<emphasis box="[1225,1283,1699,1723]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">et al.</emphasis>
2013
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Rosa" box="[1364,1424,1698,1723]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" refString="Rosa, L. C., Borzone, C. A., Vieira, J. V., Gandara-Martins, A. L., Vianna, A. X. M. R., Caron, E. &amp; Ribeiro-Costa, C. (2015) Monitoramento de Populacoes de Bledius (Insecta: Coleoptera). In: Turra, A. &amp; Denadai, M. R. (Eds.), Protocolos para o Monitoramento de Habitats Bentonicos Costeiros. Instituto Oceanografico da Universidade de Sao Paulo, Sao Paulo, pp. 250 - 257." type="book chapter" year="2015">2015</bibRefCitation>
), because of the size and color similarity, although, in this study we reviewed a 
<typeStatus box="[1061,1157,1735,1759]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">paratype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[1200,1372,1734,1758]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Bledius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caribbeanus">
<emphasis box="[1200,1372,1734,1758]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">B. caribbeanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectionCode LSID="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34795" box="[151,235,1771,1794]" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34795" name="Field Museum of Natural History" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">FMNH</collectionCode>
, and 
<emphasis box="[293,501,1771,1795]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">
<taxonomicName box="[293,497,1771,1795]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Bledius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="depressus" status="sp. nov.">Bledius depressus</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[508,597,1770,1795]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[508,597,1770,1795]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
can be differentiated from 
<taxonomicName box="[903,1073,1771,1795]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Bledius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caribbeanus">
<emphasis box="[903,1073,1771,1795]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">B. caribbeanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by tergite X, which has a dorsal longitudinal depression on its posterior three-fourths (
<figureCitation box="[815,907,1806,1831]" captionStart="FIGURES 12 – 15" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1190,1213]" captionTargetBox="[153,1426,194,1168]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,193,1169]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 12 – 15. Bledius depressus, sp. nov.. 12, tergite X (detail of dorsal depression); 13, tergite X magnified (detail of the long membranous projection); 14, aedeagus, lateral view (detail of pair of sclerites); 15, spermatheca. Scale = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/256528/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">
Fig. 
<number box="[877,907,1807,1831]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" value="12.0">12</number>
</figureCitation>
, arrow) and posterior margin with a long membranous projection (
<figureCitation box="[431,514,1842,1867]" captionStart="FIGURES 12 – 15" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1190,1213]" captionTargetBox="[153,1426,194,1168]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,193,1169]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 12 – 15. Bledius depressus, sp. nov.. 12, tergite X (detail of dorsal depression); 13, tergite X magnified (detail of the long membranous projection); 14, aedeagus, lateral view (detail of pair of sclerites); 15, spermatheca. Scale = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/256528/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">
Fig. 
<number box="[484,514,1843,1867]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" value="13.0">13</number>
</figureCitation>
), and by the shape of the spermatheca with bulbous base and 
<number box="[1205,1290,1842,1867]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" value="2.75" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.5">2.5 to 3</number>
times longer than wide (
<figureCitation box="[276,358,1878,1903]" captionStart="FIGURES 12 – 15" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1190,1213]" captionTargetBox="[153,1426,194,1168]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,193,1169]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 12 – 15. Bledius depressus, sp. nov.. 12, tergite X (detail of dorsal depression); 13, tergite X magnified (detail of the long membranous projection); 14, aedeagus, lateral view (detail of pair of sclerites); 15, spermatheca. Scale = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/256528/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">
Fig. 
<number box="[328,358,1878,1903]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" value="15.0">15</number>
</figureCitation>
), somewhat similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[613,762,1878,1902]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Bledius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fernandezi">
<emphasis box="[613,762,1878,1902]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">B. fernandezi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
illustrated as 
<figureCitation box="[919,999,1878,1903]" captionStart="FIGURES 16 – 21" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1972,1995]" captionTargetBox="[151,1432,1057,1945]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,1057,1951]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 16 – 21. Bledius externus. 16, tergite VII; 17, tergite VIII; 18, sternite VIII; 19 – 20, aedeagus, ventral and lateral view; 21, spermatheca. Scale = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/256529/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">
Fig. 
<number box="[971,999,1878,1903]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" value="16.0">16</number>
</figureCitation>
of 
<bibRefCitation author="Caron" box="[1036,1382,1878,1903]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" refString="Caron, E. &amp; Ribeiro-Costa, C. S. (2007) Bledius Leach from southern Brazil (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae, Oxytelinae). Revista Brasileira de Entomologia, 51 (4), 452 - 457. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1590 / S 0085 - 56262007000400008" type="journal article" year="2007">
Caron &amp; Ribeiro-Costa (
<number box="[1312,1374,1879,1903]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" value="2007.0">2007</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,762,2011]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">
Therefore, in this study, the distribution of 
<taxonomicName box="[708,882,1915,1939]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Bledius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caribbeanus">
<emphasis box="[708,882,1915,1939]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">B. caribbeanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is corrected, not occurring in 
<collectingCountry box="[1243,1311,1914,1939]" name="Brazil" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">Brazil</collectingCountry>
and being restricted to the Caribbean Sea countries 
<collectingCountry box="[625,718,1950,1975]" name="Jamaica" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">Jamaica</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[732,966,1950,1975]" name="Dominican Republic" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">Dominican Republic</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1026,1264,1950,1975]" name="Trinidad and Tobago" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">Trinidad and Tobago</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Frank" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" refString="Frank, J. H. &amp; Ahn, K. (2011) Coastal Staphylinidae (Coleoptera): A worldwide checklist, biogeography and natural history. ZooKeys, 107, 1 - 98. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 107.1651" type="journal article" year="2011">
Frank &amp; Ahn 
<number box="[151,211,1987,2011]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" value="2011.0">2011</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). The main morphology characteristics of 
<taxonomicName box="[684,854,1987,2011]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Bledius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caribbeanus">
<emphasis box="[684,854,1987,2011]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">B. caribbeanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are discussed below.
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/256528/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="150" targetBox="[153,1426,194,1168]" targetPageId="5">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1190,1243]" pageId="5" pageNumber="150">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,339,1190,1213]" pageId="5" pageNumber="150">FIGURES 12–15.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[346,534,1190,1212]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="150">
<taxonomicName box="[346,529,1190,1212]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Bledius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="150" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="depressus" status="sp. nov.">Bledius depressus</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[540,620,1191,1212]" pageId="5" pageNumber="150">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[540,620,1191,1212]" pageId="5" pageNumber="150" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
. 12, tergite X (detail of dorsal depression); 13, tergite X magnified (detail of the long membranous projection); 14, aedeagus, lateral view (detail of pair of sclerites); 15, spermatheca. Scale = 0.1 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1282,1631]" pageId="5" pageNumber="150">
The 
<typeStatus box="[249,347,1282,1307]" pageId="5" pageNumber="150">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[383,583,1283,1307]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Bledius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="150" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="depressus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[383,583,1283,1307]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="150">Bledius depressus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[597,686,1282,1307]" pageId="5" pageNumber="150">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[597,686,1282,1307]" pageId="5" pageNumber="150" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
was sampled in the edge of a tidal creek, located at mouth of Vaza- Barris river (
<figureCitation box="[304,393,1318,1343]" captionStart="FIGURES 32" captionStartId="9.[151,264,861,884]" captionTargetBox="[158,1429,199,832]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,193,841]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 32. Map of the coastal region of Sergipe where the holotypes of Bledius borzonei, sp. nov. and B. depressus, sp. nov. were collected. (Google Earth)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/256531/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="150">
Fig. 
<number box="[361,393,1319,1343]" pageId="5" pageNumber="150" value="32.0">32</number>
</figureCitation>
). This place is an estuarine beach (i.e., a low-energy environment) characterized by soft sediments composed by very fine sand. The samples were taken with PVC cores (
<quantity box="[1066,1130,1355,1379]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="150" unit="cm" value="10.0">10cm</quantity>
of diameter) and randomly distributed around the driftline (
<figureCitation box="[525,613,1390,1415]" captionStart="FIGURES 33" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1949,1972]" captionTargetBox="[151,1430,1204,1924]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,964,1928]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 33. Habitat of the holotypes of B. borzonei, sp. nov. and B. depressus, sp. nov. showing the drift line (seta)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/256532/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="150">
Fig. 
<number box="[582,613,1391,1415]" pageId="5" pageNumber="150" value="33.0">33</number>
</figureCitation>
). In this place, the 
<typeStatus box="[845,943,1390,1415]" pageId="5" pageNumber="150">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[989,1193,1390,1414]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Bledius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="150" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="depressus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[989,1193,1390,1414]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="150">Bledius depressus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1211,1305,1390,1415]" pageId="5" pageNumber="150">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1211,1305,1390,1415]" pageId="5" pageNumber="150" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
was found coexisting with 
<taxonomicName box="[342,478,1427,1451]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Bledius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="150" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="borzonei" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[342,478,1427,1451]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="150">B. borzonei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[499,595,1426,1451]" pageId="5" pageNumber="150">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[499,595,1426,1451]" pageId="5" pageNumber="150" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
Individuals of 
<taxonomicName box="[784,930,1427,1451]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Bledius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="150" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="depressus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[784,930,1427,1451]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="150">B. depressus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[951,1047,1426,1451]" pageId="5" pageNumber="150">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[951,1047,1426,1451]" pageId="5" pageNumber="150" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
have also been found with low abundances at some local exposed ocean beaches together with 
<taxonomicName box="[867,991,1462,1486]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Bledius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="150" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hermani">
<emphasis box="[867,991,1462,1486]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="150">B. hermani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which is the dominant species in these environments (
<figureCitation box="[318,403,1498,1523]" captionStart="FIGURES 34" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1178,1201]" captionTargetBox="[151,1432,193,1153]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,193,1157]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 34. Detail (i. e., seta) showing the discretes horizontal tumuli of Bledius borzonei, sp. nov. and B. depressus, sp. nov.." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/256533/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="150">
Fig. 
<number box="[371,403,1499,1523]" pageId="5" pageNumber="150" value="34.0">34</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
